    <br></br>
    <h1 class="sellHeading">Post an item to sell</h1>
    <br>
    <form class="itemForm" action="/gallery" method="POST">
        <label for="image">Upload an Image</label>
        <input placeholder="Image Link" type="text" name="image">
        <label for="name">Name</label>
        <input placeholder="Name" type="text" name="name">
        <label for="price">Price</label>
        <input placeholder="Price" type="number" name="price" min="1"><br>
        <label for="description">Description</label>
        <p>Talk about your piece. Is it homemade? If not, where was it purchased from? Describe the quality of the piece and remember to mention any damages. 
        <br></br>
        Adding a description helps others decide on purchasing.
        </p>
        <input placeholder="Found this piece 4 years ago at a Meadowsland flea market in E. Rutherford, NJ. Good condition with no damages. This piece was always a focal point of my living room but does not fit with the furnishing of my current place." type="text" name="description" class="descriptBox" size="20"><br>
        <label for="tags">Tags</label>
        <input placeholder="vintage, art, cozy" type="text" name="tags[]"><br>
        <input type="submit" value="Add item to gallery"></input>
    </form>

